file.name: TheTVDB API v3-3.0.0.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: TheTVDB API v3
  description: |-
    API v3 targets v2 functionality with a few minor additions. The API is accessible via https://api.thetvdb.com and provides the following REST endpoints in JSON format.


    How to use this API documentation
    ----------------


    You may browse the API routes without authentication, but if you wish to send requests to the API and see response data, then you must authenticate.
    1. Obtain a JWT token by `POST`ing  to the `/login` route in the `Authentication` section with your API key and credentials.
    1. Paste the JWT token from the response into the "JWT Token" field at the top of the page and click the 'Add Token' button.


    You will now be able to use the remaining routes to send requests to the API and get a response.


    Language Selection
    ----------------


    Language selection is done via the `Accept-Language` header. At the moment, you may only pass one language abbreviation in the header at a time. Valid language abbreviations can be found at the `/languages` route..


    Authentication
    ----------------


    Authentication to use the API is similar to the How-to section above. Users must `POST` to the `/login` route with their API key and credentials in the following format in order to obtain a JWT token.

    `{"apikey":"APIKEY","username":"USERNAME","userkey":"USERKEY"}`

    Note that the username and key are ONLY required for the `/user` routes. The user's key is labled `Account Identifier` in the account section of the main site.
    The token is then used in all subsequent requests by providing it in the `Authorization` header. The header will look like: `Authorization: Bearer <yourJWTtoken>`. Currently, the token expires after 24 hours. You can `GET` the `/refresh_token` route to extend that expiration date.


    Versioning
    ----------------


    You may request a different version of the API by including an `Accept` header in your request with the following format: `Accept:application/vnd.thetvdb.v$VERSION`. This documentation automatically uses the version seen at the top and bottom of the page.
  termsOfService: /tos
  contact:
    name: obeo
    url: https://contact.obeosoft.com/
    email: contact@obeosoft.com
  license:
    name: Apache 2.0
    url: http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html
  version: 3.0.0
tags:
- name: Series
  description: Information about a specific series
- name: Updates
  description: Series that have been recently updated.
- name: Authentication
  description: Obtaining and refreshing your JWT token
- name: Search
  description: Search for a particular series
- name: Episodes
  description: Information about a specific episode
- name: Languages
  description: Available languages and information
- name: Movies
  description: Information about a specific movie
- name: Users
  description: Routes for handling user data.
paths:
  /series/{id}:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns a series records that contains all information known about
        a particular series id.
      operationId: getFromId2
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            A series record.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesData'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/actors:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns actors for the given series id
      operationId: getActorsFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of actor objects for the given series id.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesActors'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/episodes:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: All episodes for a given series. Paginated with 100 results per
        page.
      operationId: getEpisodesFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: page
        in: query
        description: Page of results to fetch. Defaults to page 1 if not provided.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of episode objects for the given series id.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesEpisodes'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/episodes/query:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: This route allows the user to query against episodes for the given
        series. The response is a paginated array of episode records.
      operationId: getEpisodesQueryFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: absoluteNumber
        in: query
        description: Absolute number of the episode
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: airedSeason
        in: query
        description: Aired season number
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: airedEpisode
        in: query
        description: Aired episode number
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: dvdSeason
        in: query
        description: DVD season number
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: dvdEpisode
        in: query
        description: DVD episode number
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: imdbId
        in: query
        description: IMDB id of the series
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: page
        in: query
        description: Page of results to fetch. Defaults to page 1 if not provided.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of basic Episode results that matched the query
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesEpisodesQuery'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist or the query returns no results.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/episodes/query/params:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns the allowed query keys for the `/series/{id}/episodes/query`
        route
      operationId: getEpisodesQueryParamsFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of query keys as strings
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesEpisodesQueryParams'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist or the query returns no results.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/episodes/summary:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: |-
        Returns a summary of the episodes and seasons available for the series.

        __Note__: Season "0" is for all episodes that are considered to be specials.
      operationId: getEpisodesSummaryFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            A summary of the episodes and seasons avaialable for the given series.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesEpisodesSummary'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/filter:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns a series records, filtered by the supplied comma-separated
        list of keys. Query keys can be found at the `/series/{id}/filter/params`
        route.
      operationId: getFilterFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: keys
        in: query
        description: Comma-separated list of keys to filter by
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            A filtered series record
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesData'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/filter/params:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns the list of keys available for the `/series/{id}/filter`
        route
      operationId: getFilterParamsFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            A list of keys to filter by
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/FilterKeys'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/images:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns a summary of the images for a particular series
      operationId: getImagesFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            A summary of the image types and counts available for the given series.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesImagesCounts'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/images/query:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Query images for the given series ID.
      operationId: getImagesQueryFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: keyType
        in: query
        description: Type of image you're querying for (fanart, poster, etc. See ../images/query/params
          for more details).
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: resolution
        in: query
        description: Resolution to filter by (1280x1024, for example)
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: subKey
        in: query
        description: Subkey for the above query keys. See /series/{id}/images/query/params
          for more information
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of basic Episode results that matched the query
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesImageQueryResults'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist or the query returns no results.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /series/{id}/images/query/params:
    get:
      tags:
      - Series
      description: Returns the allowed query keys for the `/series/{id}/images/query`
        route. Contains a parameter record for each unique `keyType`, listing values
        that will return results.
      operationId: getImagesQueryParamsFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the series
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of query keys as strings
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesImagesQueryParams'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given series ID does not exist or the query returns no results.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /updated/query:
    get:
      tags:
      - Updates
      description: |-
        Returns an array of series that have changed in a maximum of one week blocks since the provided `fromTime`.


        The user may specify a `toTime` to grab results for less than a week. Any timespan larger than a week will be reduced down to one week automatically.
      operationId: get2
      parameters:
      - name: fromTime
        in: query
        description: Epoch time to start your date range.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: toTime
        in: query
        description: Epoch time to end your date range. Must be one week from `fromTime`.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of Update objects that match the given timeframe.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/UpdateData'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if no records exist for the given timespan
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /updated/query/params:
    get:
      tags:
      - Updates
      description: Returns an array of valid query keys for the `/updated/query/params`
        route.
      operationId: getParams1
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of Update objects that match the given timeframe.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/UpdateDataQueryParams'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if no records exist for the given timespan
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /login:
    post:
      tags:
      - Authentication
      description: Returns a session token to be included in the rest of the requests.
        Note that API key authentication is required for all subsequent requests and
        user auth is required for routes in the `User` section
      operationId: postLogin
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/Auth'
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            Returns a JWT token for use with the rest of the API routes
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Token'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Invalid credentials and/or API token
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /refresh_token:
    get:
      tags:
      - Authentication
      description: Refreshes your current, valid JWT token and returns a new token.
        Hit this route so that you do not have to post to `/login` with your API key
        and credentials once you have already been authenticated.
      operationId: getRefresh_token
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            Returns a new token to use in your subsequent requests
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Token'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /search/series:
    get:
      tags:
      - Search
      description: Allows the user to search for a series based on the following parameters.
      operationId: get1
      parameters:
      - name: name
        in: query
        description: Name of the series to search for.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: imdbId
        in: query
        description: IMDB id of the series
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: zap2itId
        in: query
        description: Zap2it ID of the series to search for.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: slug
        in: query
        description: Slug from site URL of series (https://www.thetvdb.com/series/$SLUG)
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of results that match the provided query.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/SeriesSearchResults'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if no records are found that match your query.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /search/series/params:
    get:
      tags:
      - Search
      description: Returns an array of parameters to query by in the `/search/series`
        route.
      operationId: getParams
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of query keys as strings
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/EpisodeDataQueryParams'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /episodes/{id}:
    get:
      tags:
      - Episodes
      description: Returns the full information for a given episode id. __Deprecation
        Warning:__ The _director_ key will be deprecated in favor of the new _directors_
        key in a future release.
      operationId: getFromId
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: ID of the episode
        required: true
        schema:
          type: integer
          format: int64
      - name: Accept-Language
        in: header
        description: Records are returned with the some fields in the desired language,
          if it exists. If there is no translation for the given language, then the
          record is still returned but with empty values for the translated fields.
        required: false
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of query keys as strings
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/EpisodeRecordData'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotAuthorized'
        404:
          description: |-
            Not Found

            Returned if the given episode ID does not exist.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/NotFound'
      security:
      - jwtToken: []
  /languages:
    get:
      tags:
      - Languages
      description: All available languages. These language abbreviations can be used
        in the `Accept-Language` header for routes that return translation records.
      operationId: get
      responses:
        200:
          description: |-
            OK

            An array of language objects.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LanguageData'
        401:
          description: |-
            Unauthorized

            Returned if your JWT token is missing or expired
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
